        g: '13336500', avg: 3200, histFlow: 2800, mx: 335, my: 76, abbr: 'ID',
        desc: "The Selway is Idaho\"s most exclusive wilderness river — a federally designated Wild and Scenic River flowing through the Selway-Bitterroot Wilderness with a strict permit system that limits launches to one group per day. The 47-mile permitted section offers continuous Class III–IV whitewater through pristine old-growth forest with no road access, no cell service, and no other humans. Permit odds hover around 5%.",
