        desc: "The Clackamas is Portland\"s backyard whitewater river — 83 miles from the slopes of Mt. Hood to the Willamette, offering everything from expert Class IV canyon runs to gentle family floats. Bob\"s Hole, a world-famous river surf wave near Estacada, draws playboaters year-round. The upper river flows through old-growth forest in the Mt. Hood National Forest.",
