        desc: "The White Salmon is Washington\"s premier expert whitewater river — a spring-fed, dam-free gem in the Columbia River Gorge that runs year-round. The removal of Condit Dam in 2011 restored the river to free-flowing status for the first time in a century. Husum Falls, a 14-foot Class V drop, is the signature rapid. The river\"s consistent spring-fed flows make it one of the most reliable whitewater runs in the Pacific Northwest.",
