        desc: "The Schuylkill (\"hidden river\" in Dutch) flows 128 miles from the coal regions of Schuylkill County to the Delaware River in Philadelphia. The 75-mile Schuylkill River Trail parallels the river from Pottsville to Philadelphia — one of the premier multi-use trails in the eastern U.S. The river has undergone a dramatic environmental recovery from its coal-mining past.",
