        desc: "Daniel Boone country — the Licking River flows 320 miles through the rolling hills of northeastern Kentucky, past Blue Licks Battlefield (site of the last battle of the American Revolution in 1782) and through some of the most historically significant landscape in early American frontier history. Gentle Class I–II water through farm country and forested hills.",
