        g: '03307000', avg: 280, histFlow: 250, mx: 420, my: 120, abbr: 'KY',
        desc: "A spring-fed Green River tributary in south-central Kentucky — Russell Creek flows 50 miles through cave country, fed by numerous limestone springs that keep the water cold and clear year-round. The creek passes through pastoral farm country with dramatic karst geology, sinkholes, and spring resurgences. Best at moderate flows in spring; a hidden gem for small-creek paddlers.",
