        desc: "The Maquoketa carves through the most dramatic gorge in Iowa at Backbone State Park — Iowa's oldest state park (1920), where 90-foot dolomite bluffs line a narrow Class II–III canyon. Below the gorge, the river widens through rolling farmland and hardwood bottomlands to the Mississippi. A surprisingly diverse paddling experience for the Corn Belt.",
