        desc: "The Jacks Fork is the wilder, more remote sister of the Current River — both part of the Ozark National Scenic Riverways (NPS). Crystal-clear spring-fed water flows through towering dolomite bluffs and deep forests with minimal development. Multi-day float trips on the Jacks Fork offer some of the most pristine paddling in the Ozarks.",
